description:
&lt;p&gt;A great entry level opportunity to springboard a career in clinical research within a busy Oncology Research Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Nottingham Cancer Clinical Trials Team manage a large number of Oncology research trials offering patients access to a wide range of trials from intense treatment to observational and translational trials. We are very focused on team working and all work together to be able to support patients entering trials and meet our contractual obligations with the various trial centres and companies .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for an Oncology Research Data Clerk . If you are organised, have attention to detail, have an interest in or want to learn more about Oncology and are personable and can interact well with others then this could be the role for you. You would be liaising with a wide range of staff including Research Nurses, Clinical Oncologists and external trial companies staff to ensure that the information you need to input to electronic systems is accurate and factually correct. Attention to detail is imperative and the ability to speak up and query information is also a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more details or an informal chat please call Shameem Asif- Suleman on 0115 9691169 ext 75700&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
